{
    "id": "electronics/light-sensor",
    "title": "Build a Light Sensor",
    "description": "Use a photoresistor and Arduino to measure ambient brightness.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/electronics_light_sensor_arduino_photoresistor.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Hey again! Orion here. Let's build a light sensor. Set the board on a non-conductive surface, put on safety goggles and clip on an anti-static wrist strap. Discharge static by touching grounded metal, keep hands dry, and unplug the board before wiring to avoid shorts.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "materials",
                    "text": "What do I need?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "materials",
            "text": "Gather one Arduino Uno, a breadboard, three jumper wires, one photoresistor, one 10 kΩ resistor, one USB Type-A to Type-B cable, a digital multimeter, safety goggles, an anti-static wrist strap, and a laptop with the Arduino IDE installed. Keep components in a tray so leads don't touch or short.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "arduino-ide-install",
                    "text": "Install the Arduino IDE"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "wire",
                    "text": "Ready to wire!",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "72b4448e-27d9-4746-bd3a-967ff13f501b",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "d1105b87-8185-4a30-ba55-406384be169f",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "3cd82744-d2aa-414e-9f03-80024b624066",
                            "count": 3
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "6301ff22-49c9-468b-88aa-cafedfd5dcd3",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "ffe0b74a-f111-4d66-b4c3-d82965a976ac",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "be3aaed8-13cc-4937-95d5-6e2c952c6612",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "5127e156-3009-4db4-85ac-e3ea070b68f2",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "c9b51052-4594-42d7-a723-82b815ab8cc2",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "d30d7a65-bd11-42a2-89c1-2828e990a3b2",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "b6fc1ed6-f399-4fdb-9f9d-3913f893f43d",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "wire",
            "text": "Disconnect the USB cable. Build a voltage divider by connecting one leg of the photoresistor to 5 V and the other to one side of the 10 kΩ resistor, then connect the resistor's far leg to GND. Measure the photoresistor's resistance in ambient light with the multimeter, run a jumper from the junction to A0, keep your goggles on, and ensure no bare wires touch before powering up.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "sampling-plan",
                    "text": "Wired and baseline measured.",
                    "process": "measure-photoresistor",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "5127e156-3009-4db4-85ac-e3ea070b68f2",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "6301ff22-49c9-468b-88aa-cafedfd5dcd3",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "c9b51052-4594-42d7-a723-82b815ab8cc2",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "rewire-check",
                    "text": "Voltage divider seems unstable."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "rewire-check",
            "text": "Unplug USB first. Confirm A0 is at the divider midpoint, resistor goes to GND, and no loose jumpers touch 5 V. Re-seat one wire at a time to avoid introducing new faults.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "wire",
                    "text": "Rewired. Re-test baseline safely."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "sampling-plan",
            "text": "Choose a validation strategy: (A) room-light sweep with hand shading, or (B) controlled flashlight sweep from far to near. Both require three logged serial readings that show a clear trend.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "code-room",
                    "text": "Use room-light shading."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "code-flashlight",
                    "text": "Use controlled flashlight sweep."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "code-room",
            "text": "Plug the USB cable in and upload a sketch that prints A0 once per second. Record three values: open light, half shade, full shade. Values should move consistently by at least 50 counts across the set.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify-trend",
                    "text": "Room-light data is logged."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "troubleshoot-flat",
                    "text": "Readings are flat/noisy."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "code-flashlight",
            "text": "Plug the USB cable in and upload the same A0 serial sketch. Record three values while moving a flashlight from 30 cm to 10 cm to 5 cm. Keep beam indirect and avoid eye exposure.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify-trend",
                    "text": "Flashlight sweep data is logged."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "troubleshoot-flat",
                    "text": "Readings are flat/noisy."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "troubleshoot-flat",
            "text": "Troubleshoot with power removed: check jumper seating, confirm serial baud rate matches sketch, and verify the photoresistor is not swapped with the fixed resistor. Re-run one validation strategy after corrections.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "sampling-plan",
                    "text": "Corrections made. Re-run validation."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "safe-stop",
                    "text": "I cannot get stable behavior safely today."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "safe-stop",
            "text": "Good stop. Disconnect USB, label this build as pending diagnostics, and do not leave powered hardware unattended.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Pause and continue after hardware review."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "verify-trend",
            "text": "Nice! Your log demonstrates a repeatable light-response trend with at least three observations.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "Trend verified and documented."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Nice work! Unplug the board before making changes, coil the USB cable, and store all parts for future builds.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Cool!"
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
